${\footnote The Game Buttons}
#{\footnote topic19}
+{\footnote browse00021}
K{\footnote {K} The Game Buttons}
!{\footnote EnableButton("Up");ChangeButtonBinding("Up", "JumpId(`winww.hlp', `Contents')")}
\pard{\keepn\sa140\sb140\b\fs24 The Game Buttons\par\pard}\par

The full set of panel buttons and actions are:\par\pard
\fi0


\tx360\tx800\li800\fi-800
\tab{\b o}\tab {\i Pass}, which tells WordsWorth that you want to pass this
 round. You will be given a chance to discard tiles; click on the
 'Done' button to complete the move.
\par\par\tx360\tx800\li800\fi-800
\tab{\b o}\tab {\i Done}, which tells WordsWorth that you have finished your
 move. The move will be checked for validity, and if it is admissible,
 the next player will be given a chance to play. If there is a problem
 with the word, a description will be shown on the status line, and
 you will  have to try again.
\par\par\tx360\tx800\li800\fi-800
\tab{\b o}\tab {\i Auto}, which tells WordsWorth to play the current move.

\par\par\tx360\tx800\li800\fi-800
\tab{\b o}\tab {\i Next}, which tells WordsWorth to play the current move,
 or, if a 'Next' or 'Auto' has already been done, to undo the last
 move and play it differently (WordsWorth stores up to twenty possible
 moves which it chooses from. If you keep clicking on 'Next' it will
 eventually cycle back to the original move).
\par\par\tx360\tx800\li800\fi-800
\tab{\b o}\tab {\i Run}, which tells WordsWorth to make all moves for the
 current player. 
\par\par\tx360\tx800\li800\fi-800
\tab{\b o}\tab {\i Stop}, which tells WordsWorth to stop autoplaying moves
 for any players for which you have clicked on 'Run'.
\par\par\tx360\tx800\li800\fi-800
\tab{\b o}\tab {\i Undo}, which undoes the last move. You can undo multiple
 moves all the way to the start of the game.
\par\par\tx360\tx800\li800\fi-800
\tab{\b o}\tab {\i Redo}, which tells WordsWorth to redo the last undone
 move. You can redo multiple moves. Note that if you undo one or more
 moves, and then play a different move, you will not be able to redo
 the undone moves.\par\pard

If you specified at the start of the game that cheating was not allowed
 then the 'Auto', 'Next' and 'Undo' buttons will have no effect during
 that game.\par\pard
