${\footnote Invalid Moves}
#{\footnote topic20}
+{\footnote browse00022}
K{\footnote {K} Invalid Moves}
!{\footnote EnableButton("Up");ChangeButtonBinding("Up", "JumpId(`winww.hlp', `Contents')")}
\pard{\keepn\sa140\sb140\b\fs24 Invalid Moves\par\pard}\par

If you enter an invalid move, WordsWorth will not accept it when
 you clock on 'Done'. Instead, an error message will appear in the
 status area. The possible errors are:\par\pard
\fi0


\tx360\tx800\li800\fi-800
\tab{\b 1st word must cross row <{\i n}>}  You are playing the first word on the board and you have to play
 it according to constraints which you have violated. These constraints
 are specified in the configuration.
\par\par\tx360\tx800\li800\fi-800
\tab{\b 1st word must cross col <{\i n}>}  You are playing the first word on the board and you have to play
 it according to constraints which you have violated. These constraints
 are specified in the configuration.
\par\par\tx360\tx800\li800\fi-800
\tab{\b Word has no anchor square!}  The word does not attach to the existing word structure on the
 board. You must build on to what is already there (but see below).
\par\par\tx360\tx800\li800\fi-800
\tab{\b Word conflicts with board!}  You entered a word which contains a letter which conflicts with
 a letter already on the board.
\par\par\tx360\tx800\li800\fi-800
\tab{\b You don't have a blank!}  The word you entered requires that you have a blank tile, which
 you don't.
\par\par\tx360\tx800\li800\fi-800
\tab{\b You don't have a <{\i char}>}  
The word you entered requires that you have a <{\i char}>
tile, which you don't.

\par\par\tx360\tx800\li800\fi-800
\tab{\b Bad Xword}  
The word you entered does not form all valid cross words.

\par\par\tx360\tx800\li800\fi-800
\tab{\b Can't start there!}  The word you entered must have its first letter preceded by an
 empty square or the edge of the board, not another letter.
\par\par\tx360\tx800\li800\fi-800
\tab{\b Can't end there!}  The word you entered must have its last letter followed by an
 empty square or the edge of the board, not another letter.\par\pard

If one of these errors occurs, you will simply have to play a
 different move. You will be given the option of overriding
 WordsWorth's dictionary lookups of the main word and any cross words,
 in case you wish to play a move that is not in the dictionary.\par\pard
