\tab{\b New Game}   allows you to start a new game. If a game is
 already being played, you will be asked whether you want to discard
 it. You will then be presented with a dialog box which allows you to
 choose the game type, the number of players, and whether or not
 cheating is allowed (if you disallow cheating, several WordsWorth
 options will be disabled; this is intended for multi-player games
 where there are two or more human players participating).
\par\par\tx360\tx800\li800\fi-800
\tab{\b Load Game}   allows you to restore a saved game and
 continue playing.
\par\par\tx360\tx800\li800\fi-800
\tab{\b Save Game}   allows you to save the current game being
 played to disk.
\par\par\tx360\tx800\li800\fi-800
\tab{\b Print}   prints the current board to a printer.

\par\par\tx360\tx800\li800\fi-800
\tab{\b Print Setup}   lets you control some printer options.

\par\par\tx360\tx800\li800\fi-800
\tab{\b Print Preview}   lets you preview and print the current board 
 to a printer.
\par\par\tx360\tx800\li800\fi-800
